{"label":"Why Working with Models?","tag":"tag","type":"type","category":"Thinking_BigComment","size":"653 60","key":401,"location":"4790 1990"},
{"text":"1) The problem at hand is too complex 
--- Working on it requires too much time/data/attention
--- Difficult to visualise/introspect 
--- Difficult to debug/trace

2) Repetition of similar tasks
--- e.g. creating different design of a similar product
--- Changing regularly one part of a system, make variations or product-line

3) Simplify explanation for broader public
--- Pedagogy: models as metaphors
--- e.g. interactive simulations of complex system, interactive notebook, ...

4) Democratisation of design or development
--- No-Code: allowing non-specialist to make product

5) Increase quality, productivity and affordability","color":"Khaki","figure":"Rectangle","category":"Note_NodeType1","size":"654 276","key":402,"location":"4790 2160"},
