{"label":"What are Models?","tag":"tag","type":"type","category":"Thinking_BigComment","size":"653 60","key":407,"location":"3850 1650"},
{"text":"1) Models are simple conceptual representation of a subject
--- e.g. a calendar is a model suitable for describing appointments over time
--- e.g. a set of variable and equation can be a model for describing a physical process

2) Models consists of concepts used to help people to:
--- Explain, describe a subject
--- Understand 
--- or simulate a subject

3) Types of models can be:
--- Data flow
--- Entity-relationship
--- Processes
--- and more...
